{
  "texts": [
    "In recent years, deep learning-based pedestrian detection methods have been classified into two-stage detection methods and one-stage detection methods.",
    "Reference [34] proposed a pedestrian detection system based on the FASTER R-CNN model, which accurately localizes pedestrians within their regions.",
    "They introduced the RA module to extract more useful feature maps and enhance the feature extraction capability of the VGG-16 network.",
    "This modification allowed the model to selectively emphasize informative features while suppressing less useful ones.",
    "Enhanced feature information further improved pedestrian recognition and localization accuracy."
  ]
}